Name: BALTHVS
Description: Funky but ethereal. Very spaced out and chill vibes. Would marry their bassist.

Name: Culture Shock (WORSHIP)
Description: Fast af, dancey af. I have a feeling all of these Worship guys are pretty darn good. It's simple but effective. Little builds and drops that do just the right amount.

Name: Cvbs
Description: Some kid who think I care about his feelings. (I don't)

Name: Dimension (WORSHIP)
Description: I want to run away every time I hear another good DnB mix. But then I wouldn't be next to the speakers anymore. But I want to run. Fast.

Name: Dixon's Violin
Description: This is a very relaxed, spiritual violin loop guy. Songs you can meditate to.

Name: Dombresky (Disco Dom)
Description: Hard for me to review disco classics with anything other than awe. This guy mixes those jams. If he can do it professionally, why not me?? Dope.

Name: Evening Elephants
Description: One of the rare jam band that keeps a full time vocalist on the roster. Tasty licks. Soft vibes. Funky beats. Hard not to love.

Name: H&rry
Description: Groovy kid DJ from the east coast. Smaller audience rn but he performed last year and it looked like a pretty great vibe.

Name: Jerro
Description: Relaxing and ethereal deep house tracks with vocal melodies. Vibes like the credits of a Belgian young-adult romance film with a bittersweet resolution.

Name: Justice
Description: One of the pioneers of electronic music. Legends for a reason. Two frenchies turning knobs has never been so cool.

Name: Lilly Palmer
Description: Techno music for meeting an intimidatingly beautiful european girl at a club in the underground aquaducts of Rome.

Name: Liquid Stranger
Description: Bending the rules of bass. Constant builds and drops. The intensity is real.

Name: Mersiv
Description: WUB WUB WUB WUB WUBWUBWUB WUB WUB. Ngl these dubstep guys kinda blend together.

Name: Notion
Description: Another day, another British DJ. UKG is a wild world of fast sound to bounce to. Vocal samples + synths + hi-hats + beats.

Name: Otta
Description: All about the thump shit. Nothing else matters. This is techno. This is sparta. If your mind is already blank, this is the move.

Name: Pretty Pink
Description: This house is made of butter. That's how smooth it is. Every transition is seemless. Stunning woman with a great set of tunes.

Name: Sara Landry
Description: The high priestess of hard techno. An intense auditory spectal. Have you seen molly?

Name: Sub Focus (WORSHIP)
Description: These worship guys are nuts. Speed and bounce. Makes the club go du du doot.

Name: The Strike
Description: It's like pop rock without the rock. I'd be more into it if it didn't make me feel weak. These guys sound like they'd be scared to come to my hood.

Name: Vintage Culture
Description: This is the type of music that makes you feel cool just for knowing it exists. Intense house music with thicc synth bass sounds that bounce right off your butthole. Feel it, you should.

Name: Will Clarke
Description: Bass thump heavy house music. Busy and talented dj for sure. Throws down some thicc beats with fun variety of vocal hooks.

Name: 1tbsp
Description: Decently fast paced house set, good variety of house subgenres and other cool shit going on. Mostly upbeat dancey vibes.

Name: Ahee
Description: I'm struggling with the land of wook-bass again. It does something to my ears, but I'm not sure what. Might be more of a feel thing.

Name: Ahmed Spins
Description: Chill house music with world influence. Bongos, tablas, and vocal runs from the other side of the planet. Very little released or on youtube tho.

Name: Alex Wann
Description: The house is getting deeper and deeper. Futuristic pads to boggle your brains. Transitions so smooth you'd swear they're coated in butter.

Name: Arushi Jain
Description: Princess of the modular synth. Could be a real hit or miss situation live. Good trip music. Sitting on your bare ass on a log in the woods type shit.

Name: Biianco
Description: Faster house. Plays some of the melodies and samples herself on pads.

Name: Blond:ish
Description: Groovy and chill dj sets with global influences and a fascinating variety. Vacation vibes.

Name: Bunt.
Description: Idk I can't get behind these indie pop vocals on edm remixes. Feels like I'm at a party that I have to get out of before I say something rude.

Name: Cloonee
Description: The depth of the bass has to be insane, but my AT headphones are getting maybe half of it. Would be a cool show to feel the wubz and see the bassheads. Remixes.

Name: Crankdat
Description: Headbanger dubstep vibes. Heavy heavy shit. Shaq Diesel would enjoy himself.

Name: Cydnee With a C
Description: She's got a fun little dance-pop vibe and some Trippie Redd features from the golden era of soundcloud.

Name: Eater
Description: One of the more creatively interesting bassheads on this list. Sounds like he's having a lot of fun but also making interesting sounds.

Name: Gorillat
Description: He just dropped a track with Shaq rapping on it, so I'm pretty sure that makes him my number one dubstep artist on earth.

Name: Haute & Freddy
Description: Three songs on the spotify, but there's a clear direction to their music. Reminds me of those eighties electro bands that were pre-emo (see Tears for Fears).

Name: Infekt
Description: So much dubstep it'll make your eyes pop. It's so hard for me to understand the mass appeal of this stuff, but I think it's great music for demolition compilations.

Name: Jersey
Description: Two bros on synths and decks punching out jump, old-school melodies that make the crowd churn. Should be a high energy dance set. Shades of fred again with the live beat techniques.

Name: Jon Casey
Description: Up and coming wubsmith out here doin wubby stuff.

Name: Louis The Child
Description: Djs with hit songs. They got some pretty cool production techniques for sure. Lots of variety and talent.

Name: Love, Shaun
Description: Kid is making good house music with that euro, somber vibe that makes you reminisce while doing the cabbage patch.

Name: Lowdown Brass Band
Description: Full brass section with a rapper. Woah. Extremely cool all around. Must watch entertainment.

Name: Midnight Generation
Description: Oh dear lawd, it's time to disco funk out! It's damn near impossible for me to find a disco inspired band I don't love, and this is no exception.

Name: Mindchatter
Description: Very chill pop music. Cool, simple electronic beats with calm, relaxing vocals. Feels strangely comforting.

Name: Nia Archives
Description: I'm at this bird's flat snooting bumps and chattin geopolitics, mad innit? WAAGWON MY G?? JUNGLISTS MASSIVE!!

Name: Nimino
Description: Very laid back grooves, with some edm-world hits. The type of house music you can play at a dinner party where your guests include a serious surgeon and someone's partner on xans.

Name: Ray Volpe
Description: Big wubs and womps, but a little less serious than some of the other dubsteppy guys on this list. Definitely very sound design focused stuff tho.

Name: Roi Turbo
Description: A deejay & live keys duo who absolutely kick ass. Not sure where the EF talent scouts are finding these obscure gems; they're 2legit.

Name: Tape B
Description: He gets brownie points for remixing 15th and the 1st in his lost lands set. Other than the rap remixes, it's another dubstep man to my untrained ears.

Name: Tiesto
Description: That's a 4.0 respect rating for a legit OG of a genre I don't fully understand. His sets give off an ultra-euro vibe. He's got a real good range in his sound though. 30' in the linked vid is cool af.

Name: Wakyin
Description: Lots of cool different sounding drums. Afrobeats vibes on some of the rhythms and toms. Smooth transitions, very chill, almost puts me in a dissociative state but in a good way.

Name: WORSHIP
Description: Feels like the class of DnB music. These lads are just playing each others bangers. Energy is high. Chunes are cranking. Riddims rowdy. LIMBS!

Name: Wreckno
Description: It's bass with a little bit of fun creativity. Jackson 5 remixes into deep wubby dubs.

Name: YDG
Description: More wook bass and it's just making me gassy. The beats are absurdly based and I feel it in my plums. I haven't done enough drugs to love this sound, but it's still fun.

Name: Arc De Soleil
Description: Funky bass, groovy guitars with slick grace notes over smooth melodies. Must see!

Name: Avalon Emerson
Description: Really creative and cool DJ. Her tunes are very danceable, yet thought provoking. I'm staring out the library window listening to this sicc mix, and it makes me dream about peace.

Name: Barry Can't Swim
Description: Keyboardist dj. Live drummer & band. Wavy af. Crowd pleaser but very solid.

Name: bbno$
Description: One of the best from the latest white rap wave. Has some insanely cool samples, but a couple mid hits. Made my 2024 rap playlist with lil freak

Name: Caribou
Description: Four guys laying out a spread of danceable chunes mixing every sound that can be generated with an electric charge. Real instruments and recorded.

Name: Daphni
Description: A fun brand of dance. Same dude as Caribou but solo dj set. Still good stuff, easy to enjoy.

Name: Disclosure
Description: Special stuff for house. Super interesting stuff. An expertly curated experience. Freaky good djs with artistic direction.

Name: DJ Heartstring
Description: Super groovy trance rhythms. Uptempo dance beats. This set has a 92.5% chance to trigger a full-on dance-ocalypse according to NOAA.

Name: Gashi
Description: His most recent album is unironically titled Brooklyn Cowboy. Trying to be every genre on Earth all at once is a concept that doesn't jive with me.

Name: Interplanetary Criminal
Description: Upbeat and busy house music. Great waves to break out some shuffle dance moves to.

Name: Jade Cicada
Description: Deep and heavy remixes of anything and everything. Soulja boy, Pacman FX, Eminem, Kriss Kross, the Jackson 5, Kool and the Gang. Anything.

Name: Joey Valence & Brae
Description: Beastie boys boom bap style is back! Rappers from Penn State so I should hate them, but I don't at all. I actually think they'll be solid live.

Name: Main Phase
Description: Uncommonly cool garage breaks. I didn't think the Danes were pioneers of such funky songs. Maybe they're not and this is all old hat. New to me. And killer.

Name: Maz
Description: This guy is mixing the coolest rhythmic sounds from around the world. The kinda music to ride your avatar dragon to.

Name: Mike Posner
Description: Cooler than me is a sweet song. I guess he's got some other stuff. I'm deeply disturbed by his face on his spotify page.

Name: Nasaya
Description: Emotional and poppy edm music, lots of songs with vocalist support. Relaxing vibe. Type of music the girl teaching you how to surf listens to.

Name: Pocket
Description: Fast paced, sometimes housey, someties DnBish. Wavy vibes and fun times give way to phat bass drones.

Name: Saxsquatch
Description: A sasquatch playing sax jams over smooth, danceable grooves. It may be a gimmick, but it fucking rules.

Name: The Free Label
Description: The illest of rnb bands. Sweet vocals and good vibes. Just great jams and having a nice. I'll get a cat if we don't enjoy this set.

Name: The String Cheese Incident
Description: There's a reason I knew I'd be happy at this festival despite not really understanding the electrionic lineup before buying passes, and SCI is that reason. Must watch.

Name: Tractorbeam
Description: I can't even tell if I'm listening to the right band right now. This is slow ass folk music that is only pleasant on the couple of days out of the year that I'm feeling 100% whimsical. Idk.

Name: Villager
Description: Upbeat sound. Fun, light, electronic listening. Very danceable.

Name: Zeds Ded
Description: Really wide variety of styles, causing me to really be indecisive on the genre column, but he touches on the best of everything. Generally all danceable stuff with wild samples.

Name: 1991 (WORSHIP)
Description: I'm Highly caffinated and writing code to this guys mix right now and it's soooo good. I wanna use this as the score to my debut freerunning video filmed in Poland.

Name: 33 Below
Description: Thick mid euro synths with poppy vocals chopped up into DnB style breakdowns, builds, drops.

Name: Bambii
Description: Variety of punchy bass bops with the right amount of space. Sweet vocal samples. Also would marry.

Name: Basstripper
Description: Robot voice: [DRUM. AND. BASS.]  You get what you came for with this guy.

Name: Beltran
Description: High quality tech house dj. Would be a great late night set on a run of psychs.

Name: Confidence Man
Description: Resurrecting eurotrash! A great genre that never had to die. Choreo all over the stage. Big energy. Euforia.

Name: Fcukers
Description: They got indie vocals for bad bitches over a varitey of dancey rhythms. Some house beats, some live drums, some pop, some freestyle beats.

Name: Fisher
Description: Quality house remixes. Smooth stuff. Easy to dance to. Easy to vibe to. Has the fun vibes of an Aussie abroad.

Name: Gordo
Description: Drake recently stole his flow, so he must be good. Brings an amalgamation of American flare to the genre. High vibes.

Name: Hamdi
Description: Wubbily wobbily bass drops. Pretty cool stuff for what it is.

Name: Kanine
Description: Heavy ass DnB that hits so hard I've let out about ten farts over one song. I haven't even eaten yet today, that's just how solidly these beats are hitting my system.

Name: Khruangbin
Description: This band rules. They play the tastiest licks over the best grooves. They give off an air of mystery. Not sure why I feel that way, but this band makes you feel.

Name: Loco Dice
Description: More cool house upbeat house sounds. He seems to enjoy toms in his house drums, which is cool cuz I like that too.

Name: Loods
Description: Tubular sounds abound as the loods groove the hell out of them decks. Solid.

Name: Loofy
Description: Made me swing my hips back and forth. Wanna dance to the grooves with a girl who has pendulous titties. Bumping rhythms, very house.

Name: Mochakk
Description: Bouncey energy with exceedingly cool vibes. Makes me feel like I should wear a sleek, black trench coat and thin shades at night like I'm in the damn matrix.

Name: Moody Good
Description: Checks a lot of different edm bass boxes with a good variety of subgenres in his set. One commonality: the bass is hefty.

Name: Of The Trees
Description: The drops are more than legit. I can't begin to feel the depth over the subs in my tiny monitors, but it must be majestic.

Name: Riordan
Description: Kewl and stripped down DnB vibes. Perhaps the most english of blokes. Great energy though. Hats, bass, and vocal melodies.

Name: Say She She
Description: Danceable psych rock is a cool vibe. They can drift into a groovy disco beat with some exciting vocal harmonies. Could be an exotic 80s band.

Name: Shima
Description: Exotic sounds and voices, danceable grooves, a variety of sensational sounds, what more do you want in an electronic act? Their earliest release is from June 2024, so quite new.

Name: Sota
Description: A harder style of DnB. Still a lot of fun. Big fan of borrowing sounds from dubstep and techno. Really exploring a lot with the breaks.

Name: Spoone
Description: Lotta remix/covers from popular american music. It's alright, but gives me some real frat party vibes.

Name: Taahliah
Description: Punchy, poppy, melodic rhythms. Bouncy but sad at the same time. Lots to think about.

Name: Taiki Nulight
Description: This is so far my favorite "bass" artist. Idk how else to describe the noise this guy is making, but he's very creative in his approach to the hardcore rumble sounds. Eclectic samples.

Name: The Knocks & Dragonette
Description: Gives me the vibes of Madonna, and I fucking love Madonna. The old school synths bass is making me want to do lines off a VHS tape.

Name: The Philharmonik
Description: I'm not sure how I'm just finding out about these guys. I'm watching their tiny desk consert late at night and having a spiritual experience.

Name: WonkyWilla
Description: Woooooooook shit. It's fun but this is the definition of wook bass and it couldn't be more ridiculous. I'd describe this as something like EDM's version of chopped and screwed.

Name: Zingara
Description: Honestly one of the better dubstep artists I've heard, but idk. Ladies only mosh pit!!!
